node.accessibility_caption: Photo by Meghan | travel + outdoors ✨ in California with @brendinkelly. May be an image of one or more people and sky.

node.text:
California dreamin’ ☁️ This was the first experience I’ve had where I didn’t have to hike miles to witness a cloud inversion. We got up well before sunrise, headed to the hills of Malibu and took the winding road through the fog until we reached the highest point we could go. Driving along the road overlooking a sea of fluffy white clouds was an incredible feeling—it felt like we were in a dream. ✨
-
Photo by @brendinkelly

node.accessibility_caption: Photo shared by Meghan | travel + outdoors ✨ on August 16, 2021 tagging @brendinkelly. May be an image of 1 person, standing, sky and nature.

node.text:
Left my heart in Malibu 🌾

I just posted a new YouTube video sharing what a typical (ish) day looks like for me, so I hope you all enjoy it!! I’m so excited to be posting again, as it’s something that I’ve been wanting to pursue, but always put on the back burner. I’d love to hear any feedback or video ideas you’d like to see, so drop them in the comments on the video! Link is in my bio 🧡
-
Photos by @brendinkelly

node.text:
The most dreamy stay at @soltosoulhouse ✨🌵 We spent the last few days here on our trip in California, and it was the perfect place to unwind. We slept in, cooked yummy meals, explored the property and soaked in the hot tub as the sun set. 🌙 
-
Photos by @brendinkelly
